Police have arrested a 37-year-old man following routine patrols in Tafelsig. The national public order policing reserve unit was conducting crime prevention duties on Thursday 14 November at 18:00, when they received information about drugs being sold at a premises in Tsitsikama Street. Police found 25 units of unga, 21 full mandrax tablets, three half mandrax tablets and four packets of tik. Police also confiscated R8 382.